<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFEFFFCEA5CDFE8B1F00FD4C" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFCEA5CDFE8B1D50FEAC" blockId="31.[136,879,338,365]" box="[136,879,338,365]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFEFFFCEA5CDFE8B1D50FEAC" box="[136,879,338,365]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" reason="4">
10.4. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEFFFCEA582FE8B1CC1FEAC" authority="Moldenke (1959: 82)" authorityName="Moldenke" authorityPageNumber="82" authorityYear="1959" box="[199,766,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="restingensis">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA582FE8B1C3AFEAC" bold="true" box="[199,517,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Stachytarpheta restingensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA749FE8B1CC1FEAC" author="Moldenke, H. N." box="[524,766,338,365]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="82 - 83" refId="ref35908" refString="Moldenke, H. N. (1959 - 1961) Notes on new and noteworthy plants XXIV. Phytologia 7: 82 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 5039" type="journal article" year="1959">Moldenke (1959: 82)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. (Fig. 3B)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFCEA5CDFE431F00FD4C" blockId="31.[136,1452,410,1445]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Herbs 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA594FE431F7EFE75" box="[209,321,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.5‒0.7 m</quantity>
high, branches tetragonal, not winged, glabrous to puberulous. Leaves opposite, petiole 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA054FE431B52FE75" box="[1297,1389,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="3.0">3‒9 mm</quantity>
long, blade 3.5‒7.6 × 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA400FE671FF8FE19" box="[325,455,446,473]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="cm" value="2.25" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2‒3.3 cm</quantity>
, chartaceous to subcoriaceous, ovate or obovate, apex acute, base attenuate, decurrent, margin entire near the base, serrate toward the apex, glabrous in both surfaces, occasionally sparsely strigose along the veins. Inflorescences 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA4E0FDDF1C23FDE1" box="[421,540,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.075" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="0.85" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="cm" value="20.75" valueMax="33.0" valueMin="8.5">8.5‒33 cm</quantity>
long, lax; bracts 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA7A4FDDF1D56FDE1" box="[737,873,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.9" metricValueMax="6.3" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="5.9" valueMax="6.3" valueMin="5.5">5.5‒6.3 mm</quantity>
long, lanceolate to oval-lanceolate, abaxial surface glabrous, margin ciliate; calyx 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA4A3FDF31C66FD85" box="[486,601,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" metricValueMax="6.4" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="6.2" valueMax="6.4" valueMin="6.0">6‒6.4 mm</quantity>
long, immersed in the depressions of the rachis, 4-toothed, 1 sinus adaxial, externally glabrous, nectaries conspicuous; corolla 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA791FD971D6CFDA9" box="[724,851,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="cm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2‒1.3 cm</quantity>
long, lilac. Fruit 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA164FD961A7CFDA8" box="[1057,1091,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">ca.</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA109FD971AAFFDA9" box="[1100,1168,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long, surrounded by the persistent calyx.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFEFFFCEA5F8FD4F1C36FA65" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFCEA5F8FD4F1FF8FD38" blockId="31.[136,1452,410,1445]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA5F8FD4F1C35FD70" bold="true" box="[189,522,662,688]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEFFFCEA74FFD4F1D7DFD70" authorityName="Moldenke" authorityYear="1959" box="[522,834,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="restingensis">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA74FFD4F1D7DFD70" box="[522,834,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Stachytarpheta restingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA15CFD4E1A40FD70" box="[1049,1151,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">restingas</emphasis>
of the 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEFFFCEA191FD4F1B45FD70" box="[1236,1402,662,688]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEFFFCEA5CDFD631F18FD14" box="[136,295,698,724]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA470FD631FFCFD15" author="Atkins, S." box="[309,451,698,725]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="161 - 272" refId="ref33024" refString="Atkins, S. (2005) The genus Stachytarpheta (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Kew Bulletin 60: 161 - 272." type="journal article" year="2005">Atkins 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA488FD631D3BFD14" author="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[461,772,698,724]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref33512" refString="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. (2020 c) Stachytarpheta in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 15189 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Cardoso &amp; Salimena 2020c</bibRefCitation>
). It was recorded inside a SPA of 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEFFFCEA132FD631B6BFD15" box="[1143,1364,698,725]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Espirito Santo state</collectingRegion>
: Parque Estadual Paulo 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEFFFCEA473FD071F49FD38" box="[310,374,734,760]" country="Colombia" name="Cesar" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">César</collectingRegion>
Vinha.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFCEA5F8FCDB1BB8FCDC" blockId="31.[136,1452,410,1445]" box="[189,1415,770,797]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA5F8FCDB1F60FCDC" bold="true" box="[189,351,770,796]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Collected with flowers and fruits in February, March, May, June, July, October, and December.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFCEA5F8FCFF1A7AFC35" blockId="31.[136,1452,410,1445]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA5F8FCFF1CBBFC80" bold="true" box="[189,644,806,832]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Preliminary conservation assessment:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEFFFCEA7E5FCFF1DE8FC80" authorityName="Moldenke" authorityYear="1959" box="[672,983,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="restingensis">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA7E5FCFF1DE8FC80" box="[672,983,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Stachytarpheta restingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents a restricted distribution and has small populations (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA41AFC931FCEFCA5" author="Atkins, S." box="[351,497,842,869]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="161 - 272" refId="ref33024" refString="Atkins, S. (2005) The genus Stachytarpheta (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Kew Bulletin 60: 161 - 272." type="journal article" year="2005">Atkins 2005</bibRefCitation>
). It has an EOO of approximately 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA63DFC931DCEFCA4" box="[888,1009,842,869]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="km" value="25000.0">25,000 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C259BEBFFEFFFCEA6B4FC931DC6FC98" attach="left" box="[1009,1017,842,856]" fontSize="6" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">2</superScript>
and an AOO of 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA1F6FC931AC3FCA4" box="[1203,1276,842,869]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="km" value="56.0">56 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C259BEBFFEFFFCEA1BEFC931B3CFC98" attach="left" box="[1275,1283,842,856]" fontSize="6" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">2</superScript>
. The 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA003FC921B93FCA4" box="[1350,1452,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">restingas</emphasis>
are severely degraded due to urban and touristic expansion (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA675FCB71DFAFC48" author="Pereira, J. O." box="[816,965,878,904]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="27 - 32" refId="ref37377" refString="Pereira, J. O. (2007) Formacoes pioneiras: restingas. In: Simonelli, M. &amp; Fraga, C. N. (Eds.) Especies da flora ameacadas de extincao no estado do Espirito Santo. IPEMA, Vitoria, pp 27 - 32." type="book chapter" year="2007">Pereira 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA695FCB71A86FC48" author="Thomazi, R. D. &amp; Rocha, R. T. &amp; Oliveira, M. V. &amp; Bruno, A. S. &amp; Silva, A. G." box="[976,1209,878,904]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref39633" refString="Thomazi, R. D., Rocha, R. T., Oliveira, M. V., Bruno, A. S. &amp; Silva, A. G. (2013) Um panorama da vegetacao das restingas do Espirito Santo no contexto do litoral Brasileiro. Natureza On line 11: 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2013">
Thomazi 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA179FCB61A4AFC48" box="[1084,1141,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA022FCB71EEAFC6C" author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Committee" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref34955" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 30 December 2019)" type="book" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEFFFCEA5A7FC4A1FBBFC6C" authorityName="Moldenke" authorityYear="1959" box="[226,388,915,941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="restingensis">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA5A7FC4A1FBBFC6C" box="[226,388,915,941]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. restingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be classified as “Endangered” (EN) because of the restricted AOO, number of known locations, and declining habitat quality. However, it occurs inside PAs in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFEFFFCEA691FC6F1A27FC10" box="[980,1048,950,976]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and, therefore, we adopted a more conservative point of view and considered the species “Vulnerable” VU B2ab(i,ii,iii).
</paragraph>
